[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":212},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F03\u002Ffix-teachable-blank-video-browser-privacy-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F03\u002Ffix-teachable-blank-video-browser-privacy-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F03\u002Ffix-teachable-blank-video-browser-privacy-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F03\u002Ffix-teachable-blank-video-browser-privacy-fix\u002F":187,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F03\u002Ffix-teachable-blank-video-browser-privacy-fix\u002F":196},"\u002Fother\u002F20221003\u002F1829744425\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":168,"date":169,"description":170,"extension":171,"lang":172,"meta":173,"navigation":174,"path":175,"readingMinutes":176,"seo":177,"standalone":178,"stem":179,"tags":180,"tldr":184,"updated":184,"url":185,"__hash__":186},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Ffix-teachable-blank-video-browser-privacy-fix.md","Teachable Video Shows Blank? Browser Strict Privacy Settings Are the Likely Cause","8294744251",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":156},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,37,43,46,52,56,59,62,65,78,84,95,101,104,110,113,116,121,128,134,138,143,149,153],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"A few people told me their Teachable videos stopped playing, but mine were fine. Wrote down how I resolved it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-problem","The problem",[17,25,26],{},"Multiple readers reporting blank video frames on Teachable:",[17,28,29],{},[30,31],"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"Teachable blank video","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fp1xGcwn.png",[17,35,36],{},"Meanwhile, Udemy videos work fine:",[17,38,39],{},[30,40],{"alt":41,"src":42},"Udemy works","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQgXzt6O.png",[17,44,45],{},"And YouTube too:",[17,47,48],{},[30,49],{"alt":50,"src":51},"YouTube works","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F58SOa3g.png",[12,53,55],{"id":54},"the-fix","The fix",[17,57,58],{},"Other browsers (e.g., Chrome) worked even when their main browser didn't — so this was a browser settings issue. Walking through how I fixed it.",[17,60,61],{},"If you hit this, first try opening a different browser (Firefox user → try Chrome \u002F Edge, etc.) to confirm the video works in another browser. If it does, the issue is browser settings.",[17,63,64],{},"Fix steps below, starting with Firefox since that's what most reports were from. Other browsers are similar.",[17,66,67,68,72,73,77],{},"In Firefox, type ",[69,70,71],"code",{},"about:preferences#privacy"," in the address bar. You'll see the ",[74,75,76],"strong",{},"browser privacy"," settings:",[17,79,80],{},[30,81],{"alt":82,"src":83},"Browser privacy settings","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FlCoyQXu.png",[17,85,86,87,90,91,94],{},"If Enhanced Tracking Protection is set to ",[74,88,89],{},"Strict",", that's likely the cause. Change to ",[74,92,93],{},"Standard"," and click \"Reload All Tabs\":",[17,96,97],{},[30,98],{"alt":99,"src":100},"Standard mode","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FyOLB13a.png",[17,102,103],{},"Reload Teachable — video should play now:",[17,105,106],{},[30,107],{"alt":108,"src":109},"Working","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FkIX61fx.png",[17,111,112],{},"This is a Firefox privacy-setting issue. If you want to keep Strict mode, you can add Teachable to the exception list — but that's more work, so I'd just switch to Standard.",[17,114,115],{},"Equivalent privacy settings paths in other browsers:",[117,118,120],"h3",{"id":119},"chrome","Chrome",[17,122,123,124,127],{},"Type ",[69,125,126],{},"chrome:\u002F\u002Fsettings\u002Fsecurity"," in the address bar:",[17,129,130],{},[30,131],{"alt":132,"src":133},"Chrome security settings","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FfLwVRDF.png",[117,135,137],{"id":136},"microsoft-edge","Microsoft Edge",[17,139,123,140,127],{},[69,141,142],{},"edge:\u002F\u002Fsettings\u002Fprivacy",[17,144,145],{},[30,146],{"alt":147,"src":148},"Edge privacy","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fk0cp03n.png",[117,150,152],{"id":151},"try-disabling-extensions","Try disabling extensions",[17,154,155],{},"If privacy is on Standard\u002FBalanced but videos still don't play, try disabling all browser extensions and reload Teachable. If that works, it's an extension blocking something. Re-enable extensions one by one to identify which.",{"title":157,"searchDepth":158,"depth":158,"links":159},"",2,[160,161,162],{"id":14,"depth":158,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":158,"text":23},{"id":54,"depth":158,"text":55,"children":163},[164,166,167],{"id":119,"depth":165,"text":120},3,{"id":136,"depth":165,"text":137},{"id":151,"depth":165,"text":152},"Misc","2022-10-03 09:46:45","Some readers told me Teachable videos suddenly stopped playing, but my own browser was fine. Turned out the culprit was their browser's Strict privacy mode. This post walks through the fix in Firefox, Chrome, and Edge, plus the fallback when toggling privacy mode isn't enough.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Ffix-teachable-blank-video-browser-privacy-fix","2",{"title":6,"description":170},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Ffix-teachable-blank-video-browser-privacy-fix",[181,182,183],"Teachable","Website","Troubleshooting",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F03\u002Ffix-teachable-blank-video-browser-privacy-fix\u002F","6W8LMSaC18oFhEgo-P2ascFZ4F0imirXmXcMEx9vWtc",{"newer":188,"older":192},{"url":189,"title":190,"date":191},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F04\u002Freact-day-20-strictmode-and-web-vitals\u002F","React, Might As Well Learn It Now - StrictMode and Web Vitals in CRA (20)","2022-10-04 00:00:01",{"url":193,"title":194,"date":195},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F03\u002Flearn-react-19-create-react-app-cra-setup\u002F","Learn React #19 — Spinning Up a Project with Create React App (CRA)","2022-10-03 00:00:01",[197,202,207],{"url":198,"title":199,"date":200,"readingMinutes":201},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":203,"title":204,"date":205,"readingMinutes":206},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":208,"title":209,"date":210,"readingMinutes":211},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784013066484]